\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. P. mugo} Turra, {\i Gior. Ital. Sci. Nat. Agric. Arti Commerc. }{\b 1:} 152 (1764) ({\i P. montana} Miller, {\i P. mughus} Scop.; incl.{\i  P. pumilio} Haenke). Shrub with thick, decumbent, ascending or erect branches up to 3·5 m. Twigs green at first, becoming brown. Buds ovoid-cylindrical, very resinous. Leaves 3-8 cm × 1·5-2 mm, in pairs, bright green. Cone 2-5 × 1·5-2·5 cm, shining, subsessile, symmetrical, obtuse; apophysis flat, or convex above and concave below; umbo central or below the middle, with a small mucro. •{\i  Mountains of C. Europe and the Balkan peninsula; C. Appennini. Planted for sand-binding and shelter in N. Europe}. Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge He It Ju Po Rm Rs(W) [Da].
