\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. P. uncinata} Miller ex Mirbel in Buffon, {\i Hist. Nat. Pl.}{\b  10:} 213 (1806) (incl.{\i  P. rotundata} Link). Like {\b 8} but usually a tree with an erect trunk up to 85 m; cone 5-7 × 2-3 cm; apophysis very prominent, recurved and hooked, or rounded and hooded; umbo excentric. •{\i  C. & S.W. Alps; Pyrenees; C. Spain.} Au Ga Ge He Hs It.
