\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. P. heldreichii} Christ, {\i Verh. Naturf. Ges. Basel}{\b  3}: 549 (1863). Tree up to 20 m; crown rounded-pyramidal; bark ashy-grey, flaking to leave yellowish patches. Twigs glabrous, grey only in the first year, then brown. Buds not resinous. Leaves 6-9 cm × 1·5 mm, in pairs, rigid, more or less pungent, with 2-6 layers of hypodermal cells; resin-canals 2-11, median. Cone 7-8 × 2·5 cm, slightly shining; apophysis somewhat thickened, pyramidal, with conspicuous ridges and a very short, straight mucro. Seeds c. 7 mm; wing c. 25 mm. •{\i  Mountains of C. & W. part of Balkan peninsula; S. Italy}. Al Gr Ju.
\par

