\pard\f0\fs28 Var.{\i  heldreichii}, which has a flat apophysis, and 2 or 3 layers of hypodermal cells in the leaf, occurs only in N. Greece (Olimbos). The more widespread variant is var.{\i  leucodermis} (Antoine) Markgraf ex Fitschen ({\i P. leueodermis} Antoine).
